er bunker cost is that vessel took advantage of having three bunker grades onboard and consumed VLSFO in load and discharge port while VMS calculated the port consumption basis LSMGO. However, due to wind force of Beaufort 6-7 during the last week before arrival to disport, vessel had slightly higher laden consumption than budgeted. Good news is that the savings in load and discharge port outweighed the over-consumption caused by the bad weather.\u00A0 Operationally, not much to mention besides the pre-fixing stage of the voyage. There was a lot of back and forth correspondence between NMM and Saras vetting department regarding the procedure on how to sample the ballast tanks to check for the presence of oil, especially on arrival at Sarroch. This is a weird requirement as a fully loaded vessel normally arrives disport with its ballast tanks empty, there might be minimal ballast in some tank(s) to adjust list and trim due to bunker consumption but that\u0027s normal practice. The whole discussion was finally ended by Captain confirming that he would have NIL ballast on arrival Sarroch, this confirmation was included in the CP."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-02-13T11:23:39.443","modifiedByFull":"Mohlin, Max","remark":"Port costs and bunkers updated"}],"offhireList":[{"id":197667,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":"Machinery","remark":"Planned - purge/gas free Cargo Tanks No 3 Stbd and No 4 Stbd for repairs (NMM account) - No time lost","offhireBunkerList":[{"id":262322,"gradeName":"HSBF","quantity":4.1,"price":495.0,"displayOrder":0},{"id":262324,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":7.2,"price":616.0,"displayOrder":1}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}